This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and event identification in documents. It also involves the use of sequence labelling and reinforcement learning, which are common techniques in this field. Additionally, the paper may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of supervised and reinforcement learning for training the model. It may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with extracting special events from documents, which is a common task in information retrieval. Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks for encoding documents and extracting events.
